		<description>Caliber: .30-06 Springfield. 8-round internal mag. Semi-Automatic.
		
The MC1 (also known as the MC52), is a variant of the M1 Garand (more specifically, the M1C Sniper variant) adopted by the US Marine Corps in 1951 as its standard sniper rifle. It used a commercial Kollmorgen Stith Bear Cub scope that was designated as the Model 4XD-USMC telescopic sight. As such, it is one of the only post-WW2 M1 Garand variants to be adopted while still using the .30-06 caliber, and saw service in Vietnam alongside many other rifles.</description>
